main event: Multiple UFO sightings were reported in Moneta, Virginia from January 25 to February 5, 1965, involving six distinct observations.
interesting points: The objects were described as cigar-shaped and aluminum, One sighting included observations by a crane operator and a housewife, Weather conditions were clear during the sightings, The objects were reported to have erratic, fast courses, and the sightings lasted between 3 to 10 minutes each.
witness description: a crane operator for the Norfolk and Western Railroad and a mature housewife
